values: HOMECOMING IS SATURDAY AND I'M NOT GOING TO SCHOOL TOMORROW!!!!! WHOO!!! :D

Okay, I definetly have not been keping up to date with LJ... So what's been up???     Well, I'LL TELL YA! :D

Only 5 days left til HOMECOMING!!!!! They JUST gave me my ticket today! :p lol. I cannot wait for Saturday. It's gunna be great! I've got my dress, shoes, bra, hair appointments, and makeup person MAYBE.

Today was mismatch day. It was great. I looked like a complete idiot. lol. Stacy, I, and some other girl got our picture taken for the yearbook. yay! hehe. Tomorrow is sports day. FSU BABY!!!! :D haha.

Janet's getting something for me that's gunna be UBER cool! It's a suprise so ya'll will just have to wait til Homecoming!! Rachel knows... even I highly doubt she realizes it. :p

I'm not gunna be at school on Friday. Me n some other gals are gunna be at the Barbershop Worshop all day. Aww darn, no pep rally. 0:)

This weekend has been pretty crazzzy. Friday I was supposed to go to Robert's game at Leto. That didn't work out. He ended up coming over and staying til about 4:30am.

Saturday I worked. Then Robert came over and he and I followed Dad, Janet and Dex in the Explorer to Outback in Pasco. We met up with Theresea, her son Steven, and 3 other troopers to celebrate Theresea's birthday. It was pretty fun. Haha, they didn't have a table big enough for all of us, so Dex, Steven, Robert and I had to sit at the table next to them. It was Thanksgiving as a kid all over again!! :p Robert and I left a little bit before everyone else did. We picked JR up and then we all went to some party one of the TC fball players was having. After a while we headed over to Robert's new house cuz JR hadn't seen it yet. We had a blast there. Haha, JR is definetly in denial! :p *sighs* Poor JR. Then we hung out at my house for a while. The rule is they have to be out by midnight. When the clock struck 12 guess what that meant.... Happy Six Month Anniversary!!!!! :D

Today I worked again. Then I came home, got ready and Robert came over. He brought me red roses and a pretty bracelet. I got him 2 shirts from *cough Aeropostale cough*. Yuck. lol. Haha, he modeled them for me and Janet... Yeah, they didn't have any XL and one only had medium.. so of course he haaaaaad to try the medium on first... Let's just say it was a 'little' fitting. Heh. The large was a little better but anyway.... we went out to Cracker Barrell then stopped at WalMart. He had to be home by 8 so we didn't really have time to do much. Atleast I got to see him though. We've been together 6 months now. I love him with all my heart. I don't know what I'd do without him. Happy Anniversary sweetie! I love you!

 

Oh yeah, I talked to Catrina today. She might come down for Spring Break!!! *giddy* :D

I have no idea why, but I feel really cruddy right now. I hate crying. I hate remembering the past. I hate missing people. I hate regreting decisions. I hate wanting to be one of them. I hate being decieving. I hate holding things in. I hate being scared. Just looking at myself in the mirror I cry sometimes. Ugh, whatever. I guess I sound kinda emo. Don't mind me. :x

Friday night was possibly the best night of my life.... and the craziest.

So, let's see, was today just another boring day?? yes............NOT!

Okay so here's what happened basically. First, flat tire on our way to school, need I remind you I had 3 passengers. So dad picked us up and took us to school. We were late, but no tardy, hooray! Mrs. Palma was absent so no hard work or spanish speakin teacher. :p Mrs. Crump measured all the B2R girls which was 'interesting' to say the least. LoL. I got my lunch fast which is ALWAYS a plus! :D Pretty much, all classes were shorter b/c pep rally. Which was AMAZING! Juniors won the spirit stick AGAIN! And I LITERALLY cried when the band played The Phantom Of The Opera. I was laughing, crying, and smiling all at the same time. I ABSOLUTELY LOVED IT!!!! So yeah, I'm buying a band shirt due to the fact that it has POTO logo on it! 0:) Okay, so I got home and... guess what!!! No, you're wrong. I GOT A NEW CAR!!!!!! :D I mean, 'technically', it's not my car, but I'm the one driving it so, whatever! It works for me! LoL. I'll have to post pics sometime. :D It's a BRAND NEW white explorer '05. OOH! Here's the best part= CLOTH SEATS!!! THAT MEANS NO LEATHER!! HOORAY! :) So yeah, I'm VERY happy. Then Rachel decided to come over and she ended up driving me to FUSION. OMGsh, I almost forgot how amazing it was! I missed it SOOOOO much! There are SOOO many more people that go there now. It's crazy! I saw a bunch of people I know.  Like Sam, N8, Shawna, Renee, Molly, Brian, Alayna, Alex... and like EVERYONE! :p

Well, it's hard to type and talk on the phone at the same time so... chat later!!!

P.S. I really do love ALL my friends!!!!! I'm sorry if I don't say it or show it enough. :\

So this weekend.....

Friday- Dad and I went to Robert's preseason game @ Robinson. The score was 7-0 in Robinson's favor up til 2nd quarter. Then TC had the ball at the 15 yd line.... then the ST00PID refs call the game because of lightning... I don't even think it was worth calling off for. But whatever. TC SO would've won if they'd kept playing.

 

Saturday- I worked and got to help HOST for a while! Woo!!! Then I got home and There were like 4 or 5 troopers there. Dad was having a little party for him and some old buddies on his squad. Robert came over too. He helped me with my AH homework online. Yeah, I think I'm pretty much screwed in that class right now. :x Then we went to Q-Zar which was pretty fun. Then we stopped by Payless for my chorus service project. (Yeah, I think I'm running for VP- VOTE FOR ME! :) ...Please.) After that we went to CVS to pick up some stuff then right next door to Pizza Hut. I swear, the lady took forever to get our order right. :p Then we came back to my house and hung out til Robert had to go home.

 

Sunday- Work was SO exhausting. Not that I was running back and forth bussing tables but I was on my feet for 6 straight hours and bored rolling silverware/filling pitchers/cleaning and organizing the alter/assisting the servers. I'm not complaining though. And the coolest coincidence happened. Dad, Janet and Uncle Joe came in basically the same time Aunt Karen, Thumper, and Molly did. They sat across from each other and I visited with both of them. Aunt Karen n them left right before I went on break though. So I sat with Dad n them. The last customers left at 3:15pm and we close at 2:30pm. The only reason they left was b/c Margaret had to ask them to. :\ So we didn't finish up til 4:30pm. Ugh. What a long day. Then I came home, rested a bit and did all my homework.

 

Tomorrow's the parent conference night for junior ring assembly. And I have singing lessons. I really need to buckle down with school and homework.. and classwork for that matter this year. Especially with this online class now. BTW: Does anyone know anything about the track team?? Did they already do that or has track not started yet??

First time ever seeing him play. :p

Today was an awful day. I cant' even think of why. Nothing really bad actually happened. No one was mean to me or made fun of me. Nobody died and I don't feel sick. For some reason I just feel............ empty. I've been feeling like that for the past couple of days now. It's be such a long time since I felt like that. But I just felt so unwanted and out of place today. I dunno... maybe I'm being a drama queen or emo. :\ I slammed the door when I got home and started crying.

Dad said the Suzuki gets out of the shop tomorrow and he's going to try n trade it in for an Escape or Explorer sometime soon. Doesn't mean I'll be driving anytime in the near future though. :x

Rachel came over last night unexpextedly. That made me feel pretty good. She didn't stay long but we hung out a little bit.

Oh, and last but definetly not least, today is me and Robert's 5 month anniversary. : ) I feel like I'm happiest when I'm with him and none of my problems really seem to matter. That doesn't mean I feel like crap when I'm around my friends. I love my friends to death and they make me feel wonderful, but it's different with him. I'm just so full of joy when I'm around him. I love him so much. <3

While I was walking back to my car, this disgruntled looking man starts a small conversation with me in an English accent. I said hello and asked him how he was. He said something along the lines of being hungry and if I could spare him some loose change. So I did. I reached into the grocery bag and handed him a dollar. He said thank you (of course) and went along his way. I told him to have a wonderful night and take care of himself. I felt SO good about myself. I just love helping people out like that. My dad would have been furious though. I know that for a fact, if he knew I helped the man that is. But don't worry, I took a dollar out of my wallet and added it to dad's change. I just didn't feel like getting to my wallet at the moment is all. Anyway, I thought that was very sweet of dad to let me go late at night just for a craving and I was more than glad to help the man out. :)

I recieved an e-mail from a family member of mine. It was simply just a forward. It was a poem written by Maya Angelou called "CLOTHES"... it bothered me in a way. I don't mean to be contreversial, but I found it.... I can't even think of how it made me feel..

You are in love with Tommy,
Because his last name is Hilfiger,
But behind closed doors, Tommy,
Is calling you a nigger,

But you could care less,
Because you have been taught to dress to impress,
If I ask you about your true history,
You would have to look on the back of your jeans and Guess,

You come up in the club wearing Versace,
Clothes made by a homosexual male,
So even when you say you are straight,
It is very hard to tell,
And for footwear, you wear Timberlands,

Even under the sun,
That same tree that's the symbol for them,
Could have been the same one your ancestors were hung from,

I cannot forget Nautica,
When was the last memory you have of ships,
Coming to North America in shackles,
Being beaten over the back with whips,

And to my beautiful black queens,
Whose creative womb has become barren,
I am confused because your face says Nefertiti,
But your sweater reads Donna Karen,

When was the last time you saw Liz Claiborne,
Conversing with black women,
But as soon as her name is printed on a purse,
To Macy's you quickly go, running,


Ralph Lauren doesn't even look at black men,
Unless they are driving him around town,
But as soon as that slave master appears on the back of a horse,
You put whatever you have picked up down,

My people reclaim your status in this world and in your life,
F.U.B.U. in case you didn't know, stands for (For Us By Us),
Buying black will someday suffice,
Do you know who owns Timberland fashion?

Well, Timberland is owned by the president of the KKK,
Surprised? Don't be.
Read more books black people,
Always hope for the best and prepare for the worst,
You may not get what you pay for,
But you'll surely pay for what you get.

~ Maya Angelou
